uganda re-rout coff export through kisumu long delay at the railway cross on the kenyan border have led uganda to re-rout it coff export through a ferri link with the kenyan port of kisumu across lake victoria , ugandan offici base in kenya said . uganda ha a direct rail link with the kenyan port of mombasa through which it conduct 70 pct of it extern trade but there is a chronic shortag of railway wagon , they said . custom at kisumu take less than a day compar with two to three at the malaba rail border cross , a ugandan railway offici said . `` malaba is now handl onli 10 pct of the trade and all the coff and oil goe through kisumu , `` he said . howev , an accid recent damag the wagon ferri which pli between kisumu and the ugandan port of jinja , cau bottleneck on the lake rout too . sourc at the coff market board in kampala report delay in coff export shipment last januari due to congest on the lake ferri . coff account for about 95 pct of uganda 's export earn and last novemb presid yoweri museveni order all coff shipment to be carri by rail in order to avoid the higher cost of road haulag .